        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:29PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Cheraw State Park, or 11 miles southwest of Cheraw,
moving northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cheraw, Chesterfield, Carolina Sandhills Wildlife Refuge, Cheraw
State Park, Northeastern Technical College, Cheraw Municipal Airport,
Ruby, Patrick, Mount Croghan, McFarlan, Chesterfield Ruby Middle
School, Cheraw Fish Hatchery, Alligator Fire Station, Bay Springs
Fire Station, and Chesterfield Detention Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
